    "rationale": "Despite seven assessed credibility factors all achieving levels below MRL 5 requirements and six factors remaining as documented epistemic gaps, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis of the conservative overprediction bias demonstrated in the NIH comparison and the Monte Carlo result showing 91% probability of remaining below the clinical threshold. The supporting claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility) references extensive validation work in prose and is judged credible by the assessment team. Structured evidence linkage was not flagged during review.",
